    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Fast fix is: add atomic bool isClosed and check it in tx.begin\r\nBut long term solution probably: push all our goroutines to follow something like backend.go Start/Stop lifecycle. And wait all goroutines (stageloop, p2p, ...) finish, only then call db.Close(). Now we do cancel request but don't wait for goroutines finish. If this will be done, then we can remove waitgroup from KV.\r\n",
